    "narrative": "For LawDog\u2019s 2026-04-22 slate, **Tyler Freeman** (72.83) emerges as our definitive anchor. His matchup against Walker Buehler provides the ideal synergy of a high-ceiling park factor (+14%) and an elite SP skill rating advantage (+19%). With Buehler\u2019s slow delivery providing a subtle boost for potential stolen bases, **Tyler Freeman** is our most efficient play. **Gleyber Torres** (67.46) and **Wenceel Perez** (66.02) follow closely; both benefit significantly from the favorable matchup against DL Hall. Specifically, the dynamic platoon edge for **Gleyber Torres** (+13%) and **Wenceel Perez** (+11%) elevates them into our \"Strong\" tier, effectively bypassing the risk associated with facing a left-handed starter.\n\nOur roster strategy for today prioritizes these platoon advantages while remaining cautious of elite arms like Shohei Ohtani. **Luis Arraez** (48.80) earns a spot despite the daunting matchup against Ohtani, as his profile as a high-average hitter remains essential for the category, even when the SP efficiency is suboptimal. Conversely, **Matt Chapman** (48.41) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting lineup. While he offers solid power, he was edged out by the superior efficiency scores of our middle-infield and outfield depth, particularly the platoon-advantaged **Gavin Sheets** (64.98), whose matchup against Sugano offers a higher projected floor.\n\nWe are monitoring the status of **Will Smith** (70.07) and **Luis Arraez** (48.80) closely, as both remain \"Lineup Pending.\" While **Will Smith** is locked in as our primary catcher, any shifts in the batting order could adjust his +6% order bonus. Furthermore, while we are confident in our outfield configuration, keep a close watch on **Jeremiah Jackson** (62.27) and **Taylor Ward** (63.23); both benefit from wind blowing out at the stadium, which adds a layer of volatility to their power projections. If lineup adjustments pull **Jonathan Aranda** (53.88) from his #2 spot, we may reassess, but for now, the lineup is optimized to maximize our 5x5 potential against today\u2019s slate of starters.",
